    <p>• The Tus­can coun­try­side home of Italy’s 1982 World Cup hero Paolo Rossi was bur­gled on Satur­day dur­ing his fu­neral ser­vice, fol­low­ing his death two days ear­lier.</p>
    <p>Italian news agency AGI re­ported that Rossi’s wife Fed­er­ica re­turned from the cer­e­mony in the north­east­ern city of Vi­cenza to dis­cover the home had been bro­ken into and items stolen in­cluded a watch as well as cash.</p>


